</patch>

This change adds a utility function `stripQueryParamsBeforeHash` that removes query parameters appearing before the hash in a URL. During router initialization, it checks if the current URL has query parameters before the hash and removes them if present, using `history.replaceState` to update the URL without causing a page reload.

For example:
- `http://example.com?param=value#/route` becomes `http://example.com#/route`
- `http://example.com?param=value` becomes `http://example.com`
- `http://example.com#/route?param=value` remains unchanged (query params after hash are preserved)
